@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api/v1
@authToken = {{login.response.body.token}}
@deckId = {{createDeck.response.body.ID}}

@cardId = {{createCard.response.body.ID}}

### ─────────────────────────────────────
### AUTH
### ─────────────────────────────────────

### 1. Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "victor@test.com",
  "name": "Victor",
  "password": "mudar123"
}

###

### 2. Login — run this first to populate @authToken
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "victor@test.com",
  "password": "mudar123"
}

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────
### DECKS
### ─────────────────────────────────────

### 3. List all decks
GET {{baseUrl}}/decks
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### 4. Create a deck
# @name createDeck
POST {{baseUrl}}/decks
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "System Design Tech Stack",
  "description": "Main techonologies and pattern for system design"
}

###

### 5. Get a deck by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/decks/{{deckId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### 6. Delete a deck
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/decks/{{deckId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────
### CARDS
### ─────────────────────────────────────

### 7. List cards in a deck
GET {{baseUrl}}/decks/{{deckId}}/cards
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### 8. Create a card inside a deck
# @name createCard
POST {{baseUrl}}/decks/{{deckId}}/cards
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "front": "What was the main disadvantage for clients interacting with microservices before the introduction of API Gateways?",
  "back": "Clients had to track the unique URLs for every specific microservice they needed to call."
}

###

### 9. Create a second card (for study session testing)
POST {{baseUrl}}/decks/{{deckId}}/cards
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "front": "What was the primary operational bottleneck of using a 'master microservice' for routing instead of a gateway?",
  "back": "Simple routing logic changes required a full redeployment of the entire microservice."
}

###

### 10. Delete a card
# Replace the UUID with a real card ID
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/cards/{{cardId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────
### STUDY SESSION
### ─────────────────────────────────────

### 11. Get all due cards across all decks
GET {{baseUrl}}/study
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### 12. Get due cards for a specific deck
GET {{baseUrl}}/study?deck_id={{deckId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### 13. Submit a review — Again (rating 1)
# Replace the UUID with a real card ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/cards/7fa2d258-1f7b-45db-86cd-50e1fb95da3a/review
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rating": 1,
  "response_ms": 4500
}

###

### 14. Submit a review — Hard (rating 3)
# Replace the UUID with a real card ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/cards/{{cardId}}/review
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rating": 3,
  "response_ms": 3200
}

###

### 15. Submit a review — Good (rating 4)
# Replace the UUID with a real card ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/cards/{{cardId}}/review
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rating": 4,
  "response_ms": 1800
}

###

### 16. Submit a review — Easy (rating 5)
# Replace the UUID with a real card ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/cards/{{deckId}}/review
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rating": 5,
  "response_ms": 900
}

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────
### METRICS
### ─────────────────────────────────────

### 17. Get Prometheus metrics
GET http://localhost:8080/metrics